# Architecture

## Cloudflare Stack

- **Frontend**: Cloudflare Pages (React 18 + Vite + TypeScript)
- **Backend**: Cloudflare Workers (Hono framework, TypeScript)
- **Database**: Cloudflare D1 (SQLite-compatible, accessed via Drizzle ORM)
- **Real-time**: Cloudflare Durable Objects (WebSocket hub per song)
- **No Node.js server** -- everything runs on Cloudflare's edge

## Monorepo Layout

```
midi/
  apps/
    web/            React 18 + Vite + TailwindCSS (Cloudflare Pages)
      Dockerfile    Multi-stage nginx build
    api/            Hono on Cloudflare Workers + D1 + Durable Objects
      Dockerfile    Dev container (wrangler)
      scripts/      Seed scripts, setup.sh
  packages/
    shared/         Zod schemas, TypeScript types, constants, pitch helpers
  docker/
    api-entrypoint.sh  Docker entrypoint for API container
    nginx.conf         Nginx config for web container
  docker-compose.yml
  package.json      pnpm workspaces root
  turbo.json        Turborepo build orchestration
```

## Key Libraries

| Layer | Library | Why |
|---|---|---|
| API framework | Hono | Lightweight, TypeScript-first, native CF Workers support |
| ORM | Drizzle ORM | First-class D1 support, type-safe, zero overhead |
| Router | TanStack Router | Type-safe routing, pairs well with TanStack ecosystem |
| State (frontend) | Zustand | Minimal, works well with WebSocket updates |
| Styling | TailwindCSS | Dark mode via `class` strategy, utility-first |
| Validation | Zod | Shared schemas between frontend and backend |
| Virtualization | @tanstack/react-virtual | Render 10k+ notes without DOM bloat |
| Audio | Web Audio API | Triangle-wave synthesis with ADSR envelopes, BPM-driven playback |
| 2FA | qrcode.react + custom TOTP | QR code display, TOTP verification |
| Password hashing | Web Crypto PBKDF2 | Native to Workers runtime, zero dependency |
| Local seeding | better-sqlite3 | Direct SQLite writes for fast local database seeding |

## Database Schema (D1)

Five tables: `users`, `songs`, `song_collaborators`, `notes`, `note_events`.
All IDs are UUIDs stored as TEXT. Timestamps are unix epoch integers.
Defined via Drizzle ORM in `apps/api/src/db/schema.ts`.

### users
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| id | TEXT | PK (UUID) |
| email | TEXT | NOT NULL, UNIQUE |
| name | TEXT | NOT NULL |
| password_hash | TEXT | NOT NULL |
| totp_secret | TEXT | nullable |
| totp_enabled | INTEGER | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 0 |
| created_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |

### songs
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| id | TEXT | PK (UUID) |
| title | TEXT | NOT NULL |
| description | TEXT | nullable |
| owner_id | TEXT | FK -> users.id, NOT NULL |
| created_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |
| updated_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |

### song_collaborators
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| id | TEXT | PK (UUID) |
| song_id | TEXT | FK -> songs.id CASCADE, NOT NULL |
| user_id | TEXT | FK -> users.id CASCADE, NOT NULL |
| role | TEXT | 'editor' or 'viewer', DEFAULT 'editor' |
| created_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |

UNIQUE(song_id, user_id). Enables "Shared with me" and collaborator counts.

### notes
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| id | TEXT | PK (UUID) |
| song_id | TEXT | FK -> songs.id CASCADE, NOT NULL |
| track | INTEGER | NOT NULL |
| pitch | INTEGER | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 0 (0–87 for 88 piano keys) |
| time | REAL | NOT NULL (beat position, 0–300) |
| title | TEXT | NOT NULL |
| description | TEXT | nullable |
| color | TEXT | NOT NULL, DEFAULT '#3B82F6' |
| created_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |
| updated_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |

UNIQUE(song_id, track, pitch, time) for sequence integrity. Index on song_id.

### note_events (ledger)
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| id | TEXT | PK (UUID) |
| note_id | TEXT | NOT NULL (not FK -- survives note deletion) |
| song_id | TEXT | FK -> songs.id CASCADE, NOT NULL |
| user_id | TEXT | FK -> users.id, NOT NULL |
| action | TEXT | 'CREATE', 'UPDATE', or 'DELETE' |
| payload | TEXT | JSON snapshot of note state |
| created_at | INTEGER | DEFAULT unixepoch() |

Index on (song_id, created_at DESC) for paginated history.

## Real-time Architecture

Each song gets its own Durable Object instance (`SongRoom`). When a user opens a song:

1. Frontend opens WebSocket to `/api/ws/:songId/ws?token=<JWT>`
2. Hono Worker verifies the JWT and proxies to the `SongRoom` DO
3. DO maintains a list of connected clients
4. On any note CRUD, the DO broadcasts the event to all connected clients
5. Frontend Zustand store merges incoming events into local state

Conflict resolution: UNIQUE constraint on (song_id, track, pitch, time) prevents data conflicts. Last-write-wins with server timestamps for concurrent edits to the same note.

## Wrangler Configuration

Single `wrangler.toml` with environment-based config:
- **Default (production)**: Used by `wrangler deploy`. D1 points to remote database. `JWT_SECRET` set via `wrangler secret put`.
- **`env.dev` (local)**: Used by `wrangler dev --env dev`. D1 uses local SQLite. `DEV_TOTP_BYPASS=true` for development.

## Cross-Origin Deployment

Frontend (Cloudflare Pages) and API (Cloudflare Workers) run on different domains:
- CSRF middleware skips validation when `Authorization: Bearer` token is present
- API base URL configurable via `VITE_API_BASE_URL` environment variable
- WebSocket URL derived from `VITE_API_BASE_URL` in production, `window.location.host` in dev
- CORS configured for both `localhost:5173` and `ama-midi.pages.dev`
